arStrings.szText: Ah, Deckard, do you remember the smell of the salt air on the ocean?  No shade or devil could stand in our way!
wistful. Remembering a past life of excitement.
Been all across this world since then. Seen things you wouldn’t believe, but it was never quite the same. Wandering without a direction… it was just… waiting...
bittersweet. Your youth was exciting but you have wasted your years since.
Aye, it’s important to have something to walk towards.
Thoughtful. Your companion has reminded you that living a life without purpose is a waste, something you've been guilty of.
One foot in front of the other, eh, old friend? If we stop walking, we die!
Shaking off melancholy. "Well, nevermind all that!" trying to cheer yourself up.
